        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 3:27PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hubbard Hill, or 11 miles west of Scottsbluff, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Scottsbluff, Gering, Mitchell, Terrytown, Hubbard Hill, Stegall,
Scotts Bluff County Fairground, Scottsbluff Airport, and Scotts Bluff
National Monument.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
